Lomak Petroleum Inc and StrataCorp, based in Columbus, Ohio, jointly said they entered into amerger agreement for Strata to become a wholly owned subsidiaryof Lomak.    Under the merger's terms, Strata shareholders will receive5.7 cts per share of Strata common and warrants to buy about.06 shares of Lomak common at 37.5 cts per share on or beforeDecember 31, 1990, for each Strata common share.    The merger is subject to approval by the companies' boardsand shareholders and agreement of certain Strata creditors,among other things, said the companies. Reuter&#3;